  "text": "An 100KW lithium-ion BESS has been modeled in reference to the R int model presented in [CITATION_1] . In general we know that I bat and V bat can be expressed as Eqs. (3) and (4), respectively, when the battery power consumption is P W. Moreover, as shown in Eqs. (5) and (6), V ocv and R bat int are determined by using look-up tables based on experimental data presented in Figs. 2 and 3. The battery SOC is calculated by using Eqs. (7) and (8), and the η is calculated depend on battery charge/discharge status. The model of BESS based on Matlab/Simulink is shwon in Fig.4 [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In this chapter, 1MWh BESS is designed by integrating ten 100kWh BESSs in parallel to minimize real power imbalance in micro-grid power system. ",
